{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"safe","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"index","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Index","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Element","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa"},{"text":"? { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"range simply result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Example usage:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Subscript","modules":[{"relatedModules":["Swift"],"name":"SwiftExtras"}],"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}],"constraints":[{"code":"Self","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"externalID":"s:Sl11SwiftExtrasE4safe7ElementQzSg5IndexQz_tcip","role":"symbol","title":"subscript(safe:)","extendedModule":"Swift","symbolKind":"subscript","fragments":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyw